                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d565">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.24546/6: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Nouméa</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacVitty</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nouméa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-10-22T10:00:00+11:00"
                            >October 22, 1941—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 12:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>22. Department’s 16, October 15, 7 p.m.<note n="7" xml:id="d565fn7">This telegram
                        repeated telegram No. 4458, October 15, 7 p.m., to the Ambassador in the
                        United Kingdom, <ref target="#pg_573">p. 573</ref>.</note> The situation
                    with regard to landing bases here is: three land bases are under construction,
                    one nearing completion and the other two being cleared for emergency landing
                    fields. These bases are being constructed by the local government for Australia
                    with materials furnished by that Government. All these bases can be greatly
                    improved and it is my opinion that the War Department’s needs would be best
                    served by cooperating with the Australian Government in the improvement of the
                    projects already under way here; in view of this I am not taking the matter up
                    with the High Commissioner upon his arrival here, pending further
                    instructions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacVitty</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
